14 WHEREAS, Bryan County was named the fastest-growing county in Georgia following the
15 last census, experiencing a population increase of 48 percent between 2010 and 2020; and
16 WHEREAS, the county's rapid population growth is largely attributed to its top-performing
17 public school system, which attracts and supports families seeking high-quality education for
18 their children; and
19 WHEREAS, the Bryan County Chamber of Commerce serves as a recognized leader in
20 promoting business, economic and community development, and public policies that balance
21 economic prosperity with quality of life; and
22 WHEREAS, with its thriving communities, rich history, and outstanding growth, Bryan
23 County exemplifies the values of the State of Georgia.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
25 recognize January 28, 2025, as Bryan Day at the state capitol.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
27 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
28 press.
